article.headline: Stephen F.Austin 60, Louisiana-Monroe 36
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas -- Denzel Barnes scored 13 points to lead Stephen F. Austin to a 60-36 victory over Louisiana-Monroe on Wednesday night. The Lumberjacks (8-3) got off to a quick 6-0 start and never trailed. They led by as many as 28 points late in the game. Eddie Williams added 12 points for Stephen F. Austin while Jordan Glynn scored 11 and pulled down a game-high nine rebounds. The Lumberjacks shot 46 percent from the field, compared to 37 percent for the Warhawks (4-10). Hugh Mingo led the Warhawks with 11 points.
